On my first trip here, I had noticed a guy at our table who looked like Vince Neil.
I yelled at the top of my lungs to my boyfriend, who was sitting right next to me (yes, it's really THAT loud in there) that I thought the guy sitting on my other side looks like Vince Neil.
My boyfriend tells me, "Why don't you ask him if he's Vince Neil?
"  I ponder that as I take a swig from my second liter-sized glass of beer, and decide, what the heck.
I'll ask.
Now, normally, I'm quite a shy and reserved person.
But we were in Germany, er, Vegas, and nobody knows who I am.
So what the heck?
I turn to my left, and tap "Vince" on the shoulder.
"Has anyone told you that you look like Vince Neil?
" I shout loudly enough to ensure the sound got through his long blond locks to his ears.
"Vince" turns to me and shouts back to me, "Look like Vince Neil?
I AM Vince Neil!
"  For a split second, I thought I was gonna pee a liter's worth of beer in my pants.
Then, in the next 1/2 second, "Vince" and I (still face-to-face) scream simultaneously.
I remember it either being a Maculay Culkin from Home Alone imitation (you know, the aftershave scene) or we were seeing who could do the best Sam Kinison impersonation.
It was one of the most hilarious times I've ever had.
I do believe he started signing "Shout At the Devil" at some point during the night.
I was so effin' buzzed, though, that I can't recall.
Good times indeed.

