Hofbrauhaus is a BLAST.
Here's why:  This is the best recreation of a German Beerhaus or beer hall that I've ever been to.
The whole place is designed for the long tables you sit at with your buddies to drink imported litres of beer.
There was a traditional Oom-pah band, which only added to the evening.
I went with the Hofbrauhaus lager, which went down quick.
If you're adventurous, try the stout.
They have shots aplenty.
The best part is the cougar-esque Jagermeister lady, who serves shots of Jager in a jiggar tube.
The caveat at the Hofbrauhaus is that for every shot you take, someone has to get paddled by the paddle that the shot is served on.
So if that's your thing, your shot suddenly becomes a deal.
See pictures for the details.
The food is a little overpriced, but not bad at all.
It's all imported Bavarian sausages and meats, which go well with the beer.
Think of it as a beer hall first and then as a place that serves food, too.
Our waiter looked like someone off of the cast of Beer Fest, which only lends itself towards my glorification of this establishment.
Don't park.
Take a cab and thank me later.

$13.50/beer is a little steep, even if it is the large stein.
Normally at these German themed places I'll pay around $9 for the exact same thing.
I know it's Vegas, but this is a little out of hand.
They don't fail to deliver on the traditional German experience - loud obnoxious atomsphere with music, park bench seating, almost exclusively meat-focused menu, and only German beers on tap.
Servers wear traditional German clothing seen at Oktoberfest, and it's always a nice treat to see the ladies with large mammary protuberances carrying 3-4 steins in each hand!
